In R, `+` of line head means new line. If you put `+` at end of line, R recognize the next line in script as continuation of current line.  
So,

    f1.10 &lt;- function( x ){
      exp( a ) / factorial( 0 ) * ( x - a )^0 
      + exp( a ) / factorial( 1 ) * ( x - a )^1
    }

is the same as 

    f1.11 &lt;- function( x ){
      exp( a ) / factorial( 1 ) * ( x - a )^1
    }

